    narr:Narrative_TierContinuumNotDistinctMarkets

      dct:source narr:Sample_PitchReframeReview_20260521 ;
      skos:broader narr:PositioningThesis ;
      skos:prefLabel "Expert, Team, and Org Are a Continuum of One Use Case, Not Distinct Markets" ;
      skos:note "Scarlet's resolution of the apparent tension between the B2C primary market claim and the enterprise-centered Tranche-1 ICP: the tiers are not separate markets. The core use — capturing decision-making over time and driving AI from the resulting perspective — is identical whether one person or a whole organization is doing it. The only variable is how many people write to and read from the perspective. There is a natural evolution along that axis: a solo Expert user's perspective feeds into a Team project; a Team grows into an Org. Leading with the enterprise or organizational shape does not supersede or contradict the B2C framing." ;
      narr:theme "Expert, Team, and Org tiers are a continuum of one use case differentiated only by the number of people writing to and consuming the perspective — not by distinct market segments" ;
      narr:supports narr:Narrative_B2CPivot .

